xsl:if.h4: Because the amount of detailed information for all of the assets that have passed analysis can be considerable, such information is not included in the main report due to web browser constraints when transforming large amounts of XML data. Therefore, if you would like to review and evaluate detailed information for a particular object that has passed analysis, follow these steps:

ol.li: Using Windows Explorer Search, search the passed assets directory for the name or ID of the object and determine to which XML file it belongs.
Open the XML file from the search results in a web browser, or go to the Assets that Passed Analysis section of the main report and click the report containing the object that you want to view.
In the passed assets report, search for the name or ID of the object that you want to view.
